-- UBS’s Ziglio Leaves Role as Fixed-Income Strategist in London
-- B y   E m m a   C h a r l t o n
-- 2012-12-17T13:31:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-17/ubs-s-ziglio-leaves-role-as-fixed-income-strategist-in-london.html
Gianluca Ziglio, a fixed-income
strategist at  UBS AG (UBSN) , Switzerland’s biggest bank, has left the
firm after more than two years.  London-based Ziglio confirmed by e-mail today that he was
made redundant from the Zurich-based lender on Dec. 14. UBS
spokesman Oliver Gadney declined to comment when contacted by e-
mail.  Ziglio worked at UBS from June 2010 and was previously
employed by WestLB AG and Goldman Sachs Group Inc, according to
data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Emma Charlton in London at 
 echarlton1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Dobson at 
 pdobson2@bloomberg.net  